notes): The Door is that of a house in Verona (v. 34), formerly owned by an aged (v. 4) bachelor or widower (v. 6) named Balbus, after whose death (v. 6) it came into the possession of his son (v. r) Caecilius, who thereupon married (v. 6) and brought horne a young and lively widow (v. 20) from Brixia (v. 32), who claimed to be also a maid (v. 19).
